ing: 1 pound skinless, boneless chicken breast halves - cut into 1 inch cubes
1 (28 ounce) can diced tomatoes with juice
1 pound frozen cooked shrimp without tails
des: "This recipe came about from a lot of experimenting over the years. My family and friends like this version the best. Serve over cooked rice."
ins:
In a slow cooker, mix the chicken, sausage, tomatoes with juice, onion, green bell pepper, celery, and broth. Season with oregano, parsley, Cajun seasoning, cayenne pepper, and thyme.
Cover, and cook 7 to 8 hours on Low, or 3 to 4 hours on High. Stir in the shrimp during the last 30 minutes of cook time.
